   "source": [
    "### Impulse Response Functions\n",
    "\n",
    "Orthogonalized IRFs show how a 1-standard-deviation positive oil shock propagates to each financial market \n",
    "over 20 trading days. Confidence bands are from Monte Carlo bootstrap (500 replications).\n",
    "\n",
    "**Cholesky ordering reminder:** `[r_oil, r_sp500, r_gold, r_bond]`. \n",
    "The shock is identified as a 1-σ innovation to oil returns. Because oil is ordered first, \n",
    "the oil shock is pure — it does not include any contemporaneous feedback from stocks, gold, or bonds.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 34,
   "id": "2pz698oe3ok",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
